= MATTER-S-24-00249 Cover Letter

\

Dear Editor,

I am writing to submit our manuscript entitled "Pushing the Pareto front of band gap and permittivity: ML-guided search for dielectric materials" for consideration for publication in Matter.

Our work presents a novel high-throughput workflow that combines element substitution, machine learning (ML) pre-screening, ab initio simulation, and human expert intuition to efficiently explore the vast space of unknown materials for potential dielectrics. This has led to the successful synthesis and characterization of two novel dielectrics, CsTaTeO6 and Bi2Zr2O7.

The key advance of our method lies in the deployment of ML in a multi-objective optimization setting with a concave Pareto front. Unlike prior ML-for-materials-discovery efforts which have focused on single-objective optimization such as maximizing hardness, we argue and provide evidence that the inverse correlation between band gap and dielectric constant actually makes the task more amenable to ML as it reduces the need for extrapolation. Separate models for band gap and permittivity can each operate in regions of good training support while still predicting materials of exceptional merit.

We believe our paper is a great fit for Matter because it not only uncovers novel dielectric materials but also demonstrates a scalable, transferable methodology for multi-objective materials design. This effectively leverages the combined power of statistical inference, ab initio simulation, and experimental expertise. Our findings will be of interest to a broad readership in materials science, particularly those interested in the application of machine learning to materials discovery.

Thanks for your consideration!
Sincerely,
Janosh Riebesell, T. Wesley Surta, Rhys Goodall, Michael W Gaultois, Alpha A Lee

